Great! Let's make it a bit more interactive. How about we create a simple function that greets you based on the time of the day? Here's an example:
```javascript
function greet() {
    var hour = new Date().getHours();

    if (hour >= 6 && hour < 12) {
        return "Good morning!";
    } else if (hour >= 12 && hour < 18) {
        return "Good afternoon!";
    } else {
        return "Good evening!";
    }
}

console.log(greet());
```

Now, when you run this code, it will greet you differently depending on the current time of the day. Give it a shot!
